From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Fix C++ integer literals in demo01root.py

demo01root.py used C++ unsigned-long literals (64ul) in a Python source
file, which is a SyntaxError. Use plain Python integers.
---
--- a/Examples/demo01root.py
+++ b/Examples/demo01root.py
@@ -45,7 +45,7 @@
     eventNumber = array('l',[0])
     processIds = array('L',[0,0])
     treeBuffer = RootIOBuffer()
-    treeBuffer.init(64ul * 1024ul * 1024ul)
+    treeBuffer.init(64 * 1024 * 1024)
     tree.Branch("ev_number", eventNumber, "ev_number/I")
     tree.Branch("proc_ids", processIds, "proc_ids[2]/l")
     tree.Branch("type", ROOT.addressof(treeBuffer, 'kind'), "type/B")
